# Update Documentation Before Push

Before commit/push, check whether docs need updates.

## Primary files to check

- `README.md`
- `.env.example`
- `CHANGELOG.md` (if present)
- `SECURITY.md` (if present)

## Triggers for docs updates

- New or changed features/components/APIs.
- New or changed environment variables.
- Architecture changes (for example UI-only vs optional CMS runtime).
- Security/privacy changes (headers, consent, cookies, external services).
- Dependency changes that affect setup or behavior.

## Usually no docs update needed

- Pure refactors without behavior/API changes.
- Test-only changes.
- Formatting-only changes.
